(15, 'FULL DAY SHIRAZ CITY TOUR', 9, 37, 40, '8 hrs', 'SAADI TOMB, HAFEZ TOMB, ERAM GARDEN, AFIFABAD GARDEN, DARVAZE QURAN(CITY GATES), KHAJOOYE KERMANI, ARGE KARIMKHAN, PARS MUSEUM, VAKIL BATH & BAZAAR, NARENJESTANE QAVAM, ZINATOLMOLK MANSION, NASIROLMOLK MOSQUE', '<p><span class=\"metin\">Shiraz is the fifth most populous city of Iran and the capital of Fars Province. In 2009 the population of the city was 1,455,073. Shiraz is located in the southwest of Iran on the Roodkhaneye Khoshk (Dry river) seasonal river. It has a moderate climate and has been a regional trade center for over a thousand years. It is regarded as one of the oldest cities of ancient Persia.&nbsp;Shiraz is known as the city of poets, literature, wine and flowers. It is also considered by many Iranians to be the city of gardens, due to the many gardens and fruit trees that can be seen in the city.&nbsp;The driver will pick you up at the hotel. First, you visit&nbsp;Karim khan Citadel, Pars museum and Vakil Bazaar &amp; Bath. Then you will visit Najenjestan,&nbsp;Zinatolmolk Mansion&nbsp;and&nbsp;Nasirolmolk Mosque&nbsp;which is one of the most beautiful mosques in Iran. You will have lunch at a restaurant in&nbsp;Vakil Bazaar. After lunch the tour goes on with a visit of tombs of Persian poets- Hafiz and Saadi. Gardens are the next stops in this amazing tour. You will finish by visiting Darvaze Quran (gates of Shiraz) and Khajoouye Kermani. The driver take you to your hotel in the end</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span class=\"metin\"><strong>Available Guiding Language(s):</strong> <br />&bull; Local tour guide (Monolingual)<br />&bull; English, Italian, Persian <br /><br /><strong>Included Services:</strong><br />&bull; Admission fees for museums, tombs and gardens<br />&bull; All sightseeing mentioned in the itinerary<br />&bull; Snack<br />&bull; Pickup from and drop off to city center hotels<br />&bull; Land transportation by air-conditioned non-smoking vehicle&nbsp; <br /><br /><strong