(22, 'FULL DAY MEYMAND TOUR', 13, 37, 40, '8 hrs', 'Meymand Cave Village', '<p><span class=\"metin\">The driver will pick you up at your hotel. He will take you to&nbsp;<strong>Meymand&nbsp;Village</strong>. Meymand is believed to be a primary human residence in the Iranian Plateau, dating back to 12,000 years ago. Many of the residents live in the 350 hand-dug houses amid the rocks, some of which have been inhabited for as long as 3,000 years. Stone engravings nearly 10,000 years old are found around the village, and deposits of pottery nearly 6,000 years old attest to the long history of settlement at the village site.The tour ends after having lunch at Sarcheshme town. The driver will drop you off at your hotel.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span class=\"metin\"><strong>Available Guiding Language(s):</strong> <br />&bull; Local tour guide (Multilingual)<br />&bull; English, Italian, Persian <br /><br /><strong>Included Services:</strong><br />&bull; All sightseeing mentioned in the itinerary<br />&bull; Snack<br />&bull; Pickup from and drop off to city center hotels<br />&bull; Land transportation by air-conditioned non-smoking vehicle <br /><br /><strong>Excluded Services:</strong><br />&bull; Admission fees<br />&bull; Tips to the guide &amp; driver (Optional)</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span class=\"metin\">&bull;&nbsp;This tour operates with minimum <strong>2</strong> booking.<br />&bull; In the rare event of lack of availability due to special events an alternative day or service may be advised.<br />&bull; Amendments are upon availability and may require supplement fee.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Full cancellation applies in the event of No-Show.<br />&bull; Hotel pickups from outside of city center is upon availability and may require supplement fee. </span></p>\r\n<hr size=\"1\" />\r\n<p><span class=\"metin\">Tax:&nbsp;Included <br /></span></p>\r\n<hr size=\"1\" />\r\n<p><span class=\"metin\">Cancellation Policy: This service can be cancelled without any penalties&nbsp;<strong>4</strong>&nbsp;day(s) prior to first service date. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span class=\"metin\"><strong>Departure Time:</strong><br />9:00<br />Hotel pick ups are before this time. Additional information will be provided on your confirmation voucher.<br /><br /><strong>Departure Point:</strong><br />Centrally located hotels in Kerman<br /><br /><strong>Duration:</strong><br />8 Hours (approx.)<br /><br /><strong>Ending Point:</strong><br />Returns to the original departure point<br /><br /><strong>Additional Info:</strong><br />&bull; Clients must be ready at the departure point 15 minutes before the exact departure time.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017/05/01', '2018/03/01', 0, '', '', 3, 3, 0, 1, 1495099285, 1495099285, 0),
(23, 'HALF DAY KERMAN CITY TOUR', 13, 37, 40, '4 hrs', 'GANJE ALIKHAN MUSEUM, BAGHE HARANDI MUSEUM, JABALIYE DOME, COIN MUSEUM, GRAND MOSQUE, ZOROASTRIANS` FIRE TEMPLE', '<p><span class=\"metin\">Kerman is the largest and most developed city in the Kerman Province and the most important city in South-East Iran. It is one of the largest cities of Iran in terms of area. Kerman is famous for its long history and strong cultural heritage. The city is home to many historic mosques and Zoroastrian fire temples. Kerman is also on the list of the recent world\'s 1000 cleanest cities. Kerman is also a former capital of Iran, a position that it held during several periods. It is located on a large, flat plain, 1,036&nbsp;km (643&nbsp;mi) south of Tehran, the capital of Iran.&nbsp;The driver picks you up at the hotel. Tour starts with Kerman Old Bazaar, Ganjali Khan Complex (Bath &amp; Museum)&nbsp;and after that a visit of Harandi Garden/Museum. It continues with Yakhchal Ice House, Grand Mosque and Zoroastrians\' fire temple. The driver will take you to your hotel after visiting Jabaliye Dome and this wonderful city tour of Kerman ends at 7:30 pm.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span class=\"metin\"><strong>Available Guiding Language(s):</strong> <br />&bull; Local tour guide (Monolingual)<br />&bull; English, Italian, Persian <br /><br /><strong>Included Services:</strong><br />&bull; All sightseeing mentioned in the itinerary<br />&bull; Snack<br />&bull; Pickup from and drop off to city center hotels<br />&bull; Land transportation by air-conditioned non-smoking vehicle &nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><br /><strong>Excluded Services:</strong><br />&bull; Admission fees for all sights stated in the itinerary<br />&bull; Tips to the guide &amp; driver (Optional)<br />&bull; Meals / beverage<br />&bull; Personal expenses</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span class=\"metin\">&bull;&nbsp;This tour operates with minimum&nbsp;<strong>2</strong> passengers booking.<br />&bull; In the rar