(30, 'KISH HISTORICAL SITES TOUR', 41, 37, 40, '4 hours', 'Green Tree/Harireh & Kariz Historical city', '<p><span style=\"font-family: DefaultFont;\">Driver picks you up at your hotel. You will visit Underground City of Kariz which is more than 2,500 years old, and currently it has been converted into an underground town, then you will see Green Tree Park with the oldest trees on the island. After that you will see The Ancient Town of Harireh; the ruins display mortar masses and stone - made buildings in an area of some 3 by 1 kilometer long. The structures have been built of sand stones with some plaster layers on the walls. Some of the structures that they once ounce used to contain many floors. The antiquity of Harireh town is estimated to be at 800 years illustrating the past flourishing economy of Kish Island. It is also perceived that this town has most likely been destroyed when rocked by a powerful earthquake. Next stop is Bagho Old Village and Greek Ship\'s Beach. Driver drops you off at your hotel in the end.</span></p>', '<p><span class=\"metin\"><strong>Available Guiding Language(s):</strong> <br />&bull; Local tour guide (Monolingual)<br />&bull; English, Persian <br /><br /><strong>Included Services:</strong><br />&bull; All sightseeing mentioned in the itinerary &nbsp;<br />&bull; Pick up from and drop off to city center hotels <br /><br /><strong>Excluded Services:</strong><br />&bull; Tips to the guide and driver (optional)<br />&bull; Meals / beverage<br />&bull; Personal expenses</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span class=\"metin\">&bull;&nbsp;This tour operates with minimum <strong>2 </strong>booking.<br />&bull; In the rare event of lack of availability due to special events an alternative day or service may be advised.<br />&bull; Amendments are upon availability and may require supplement fee.<br />&bull;&nbsp;Full cancellation applies in the event of No-Show.<br />&bull; Hotel pickups from outside of city center is upon availability and ma