(115, 104, 1, 'layout_post', 'HTML', 'Details about the Transfer service', 0, '<p>We provide our customers with airport transfers in Tehran and other big cities of Iran. Our dedicated team and driver are with from the moment you land in Iran. They try their best to fulfill your needs and make your trip an enjoyable one!</p>', 1, '', 1),
(114, 103, 2, 'layout_post', 'HTML', 'What is Daily Tour', 0, '<p>We organize half-day or full-day tours in different cities of Iran for you. You can choose from our diverse options available on the website or simply contact us for a tailor-made request. We are pleased to provide travel services for our dear guests and help them enjoy their trip to Iran and experience unforgettable moments in this ancient land which is also famous for its hospitabily!</p>', 1, '', 1),
(116, 105, 1, 'layout_post', 'HTML', 'All about the Visa', 0, '<p>In order to travel to Iran for tourism and general purposes you need a tourist visa. There are two types of tourist visa for Iran:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1- Standard Tourist Visa : This visa is issued ahead of your travel date and you received it at one of Iran&rsquo;s embassies, consulates or mailed to you before your planned departure to Iran. Good for those who like to plan ahead and make sure everything is in order before boarding the airplane.</p>\r\n<p>2- Iran Visa On Arrival (VOA) or Iran airport visa: You apply and get this visa up on arrival. The scope and purpose of the visa is to give a number of nationalities to get their visa at the main entrance gateways of Iran like Tehran, Isfahan, Shiraz, Tabriz Kish and Mashahd airport and more recently at a couple southern ports of Iran at the Persian gulf.<br /> There are pros and cons to either of these visa categories. The Visa on arrival is a relatively new thing and works great most of the time but not always. It is perhaps a great option if you like to take the chance and get your visa up on arrival. The Visa on arrival is cheaper because you don&rsquo;t pay us that $60 for the processing fee but you are still going to have to pay for consular fees when you are receiving your visa.</p>\r\n<p>Here is a fee schedule for your reference:</p>\r\n<p>Note: Visa on arrival fees that you need to pay in cash at the airport to get your visa. Add to that some 20 Euro for the Travel insurance fees. These fees are subject to change at around March of each year .</p>', 1, '', 1),
(9, 9, 1, 'photogallery', '', 'Gallery', 0, '', 1, '', 1),
(118, 107, 1, 'layout_post', 'HTML', 'Iranian travel agency | invitation letter for Iran visa', 0, '<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<div class=\\\"blog\\\">\r\n<div class=\\\"clear\\\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>According to the regulations of the Iranian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, a tourist visa is issued to foreign nationals wishing to travel to Iran individually or in groups in order to visit the country, or visit their friends and relatives. This visa is issued for a maximum stay of 30 days with a possibility of extension in Iran. The visa is valid for a period of 3 months from the date of issue. Depending on your nationality and the consulate you depend on, you can submit your documents to obtain a visa in a few days with authorization code or letter of invitation (see below). Most consulates require an authorization number from the Foreign Ministry in Tehran. Without this authorization number, it is not possible to guarantee that the visa will be granted. Obtaining this approval is the most important step in the visa application, after which there will be not much left to do. You will have your visa in two weeks (or even 1 or 2 days in case of emergency visa). Persevoyages as an <strong>Iranian travel agency in Paris</strong> offers the obtaining of <strong>letter of invitation for Iran visa</strong> service as well as visa collecting service.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<h3>1. Get the invitation letter (authorization code or authorization number)</h3>\r\n<p>After receiving your application form (button below) and your scanned passport, the official request will be submitted to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and will be subject to a formal procedure. At the end of the procedure a letter of authorization will be issued and then faxed to the Iranian consulate that you have indicated in the form. We will give you the reference code of this letter that allows you to apply for your visa. This code is only valid for the consulate mentioned and only for 1 month from the date of issue (though there is the possibility of an extension but not exceeding 3 months).</p>\r\n<h3>2. Collecting the visa from the consulate</h3>\r\n<p>When you have the reference code, you will need to refer to the consulate with your passport (original) <sup>(1)</sup>, travel insurance <sup>(2)</sup>, the completed visa application form <sup>(3)</sup> (obtainable from the consulate or downloadable from their <a href=\\\"http://amb-iran.fr/fr/consulat/visa/demande_visa.pdf\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\">website </a>or <a href=\\\"http://www.persevoyages.fr/sites/default/files/demande_visa.pdf\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\">here </a>), 2 passport sized photos (3 * 4, white background, with hair covered for ladies for some consulates), visa fees and authorization number (always check the required documents with the consulate, since there may be different rules in different consulates). You can also send documents and receive the visa by mail (<a href=\\\"http://amb-iran.fr/fr/consulat/visa.htm#Visa_de_tourisme\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\">Tourist Visa</a>). Please contact the consulate for details.<br />Normally, the time for obtaining a visa is about 2 weeks (it can still be obtained within 48 hours in case of emergency or even within 24 hours if you insist, and if you provide proof). The fee is &euro; 75 (for the urgent visa) and 50 &euro; (for normal visa). You can pay by credit card at the Iranian Embassy.<br />From the moment you got your visa, you have 3 months to go to Iran, then your visa will be valid for the period you have chosen, the date of your arrival in Iran will be the first day of your visa .</p>\r\n<p class=\\\"strong\\\">As of now, it is mandatory for the applicants to have their fingerprint taken at the embassy. The applicants have therefore to attend in person to register their fingerprints.</p>\r\n<hr class=\\\"dashed-line\\\" />(<strong class=\\\"strong\\\">1</strong>) Your passport must be valid for the next 6 months by the time you apply for the visa.<br />\r\n<p>(<strong class=\\\"strong\\\">2</strong>) As for the insurance, if you have a Visa credit card, ask for a certificate from your bank manager. Generally, travel insurance is included in the contract.</p>\r\n(<strong class=\\\"strong\\\">3</strong>) Preferably, the application form must be completed on the computer. Consulate may refuse to accept handwritten application forms.<br /><br />\r\n<p>For more information about sending your documents, we invite you to <a href=\\\"http://www.amb-iran.fr/fr/contact.htm\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\">Contact </a>the Iranian Embassy in Paris.</p>\r\n<p>Please complete the form below for each passenger and send us the scanned passports for all travelers to info@globaltourismpro.com. These documents will be needed to start the process. The fee for the service is 25.99 &euro; per applicant. Once the form is completed, the payment details will be sent to you by email.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><a style=\\\"color: #3366ff !important;\\\" href=\\\"client/visa/new\\\">APPLICATION FORM FOR AUTHORISATION NUMBER</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, '', 1),
(3, 3, 1, 'layout_post', 'HTML', 'About', 0, '<p><span style=\\\"font-family: DefaultFont; color: #993300;\\\">Who is GlobalTourismPro Company?</span><br /><span style=\\\"font-family: DefaultFont;\\\">GlobalTourismPro is a travel services provider based in Bratislava, Slovakia. We are honored to provide Transfers and Daily Tours for our clients.<br /><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\\"font-family: DefaultFont; color: #993300;\\\">Benefits of booking with GlobalTourismPro :</span><br /><span style=\\\"font-family: DefaultFont;\\\">&bull; It is a B2B and B2C provider of tourism services. </span><br /><span style=\\\"font-family: DefaultFont;\\\">&bull; Book online, get instant confirmation, print your vouchers immediately. </span><br /><span style=\\\"font-family: DefaultFont;\\\">&bull; We are local, we are at your clients\\\' service at the service points, we are one local phone away. </span><br /><span style=\\\"font-family: DefaultFont;\\\">&bull; We speak your language, our tour guides speaks English, French, German, Italian... </span><br /><span style=\\\"font-family: DefaultFont;\\\">&bull; The richest product inventory, and we are adding new ones every week. </span><br /><span style=\\\"font-family: DefaultFont;\\\">&bull; Best rates on the internet, one stop for all extra services.</span></p>', 1, '', 1),
