n Tabatabaei house. Then we will drive to IKA airport for departure flight.</p>', '', 61, 0, 1493479856, 0),
(18, 'HOW I LEAVE FEEDBACK?', 'how-i-leave-feedback', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You can easily leave feedback for us in the comments part of any posts on the website. We would be glad to hear your ideas about our services so go ahead and let us know what you think!</span></p>', 'feedback,comment', 75, 1, 1493757502, 0),
(19, 'TRAVEL DOCUMENTS', 'travel-documents', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><strong>Passport</strong> Validity: your <strong>passport</strong> must be valid for a minimum period of 6 months from the date a <strong>visa</strong> application for <strong>Iran</strong> is submitted.</span></p>', 'travel,documents,iran', 75, 1, 1493757569, 0),
(20, 'CHANGES AND CANCELLATION', 'changes-and-cancellation', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">You can make changes to your bookings or cancel the service you have chosen before the deadline. If you have any further questions or you want to make amendments to your service please kindly contact our dedicated team via tickets.&nbsp;</span></p>', 'cancellation,changes,amendment,service,product', 75, 1, 1493757590, 0),
(21, 'INSURANCE', 'insurance', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">In 2011 it became compulsory to have <em>travel insurance</em> to get a visa to <em>Iran</em>. When looking for a policy, make sure <em>Iran</em> is actually covered it is mandatory to have a Insurance in Iran and you will be asked for it by the time you land in the country, it would very smart to have it before you arrive in Iran. You will not only save time in the qeue at the arrival but also be covered but a more extensive and reliable insurance.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Your insurance policy must clearly state that it is <strong>valid for Iran to be accepted by the immigration officers</strong>.&nbsp;We do not recommend an Iranian Travel Insurance company cause due to the international sanctions it could be extremely difficult&nbsp;to recover the money you spent&nbsp;after leaving&nbsp;the country.</span></p>', 'insurance,iran,travel', 75, 1, 1493757608, 0),
(22, 'MONEY & EXCHANGE ADVICE', 'money-exchange-advice', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Currency in Iran is Iranian Rial but you will find the real currency that people use is called \"Toman\" which has one zero less than the official Rial. Iranian parliament is going to decide on changing the official currency to Toman in near future. Debit and credit cards won&rsquo;t work in Iran. There are no cash machines that accept UK bank cards. It is usually not possible to change travellers&rsquo; cheques. You should bring enough hard currency with you ($US or Euros). It is illegal to change money on the street.</span></p>', 'money,currency,iran', 75, 1, 1493757624, 0),
(23, 'HEALTH ADVICE BEFORE YOU TRAVEL', 'health-advice-before-you-travel', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Visit your health professional at least 4 to 6 weeks before your trip to check whether you need any vaccinations or other preventive measures. Country specific information and advice is published by the National Travel Health Network and Centre on the <a href=\"http://travelhealthpro.org.uk/country-information/\" rel=\"external\">TravelHealthPro website</a> and by NHS (Scotland) on the <a href=\"http://www.fitfortravel.nhs.uk/destinations.aspx\" rel=\"external\">fitfortravel website</a>. Useful information and advice about healthcare abroad is also available on the <a href=\"http://www.nhs.uk/NHSEngland/Healthcareabroad/Pages/Healthcareabroad.aspx\" rel=\"external\">NHS Choices website</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Medical facilities are reasonable in the major cities but poor in remote areas. Many health professionals speak some English. Make sure you have adequate travel health insurance and accessible funds to cover the cost of any medical treatment abroad and repatriation.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">If you need emergency medical assistance during your trip, dial 115 and ask for an ambulance. You should contact your insurance/medical assistance company promptly if you are referred to a medical facility for treatment</span></p>', 'health,advice,iran', 75, 1, 1493757828, 0);
